<dl><dt>Interviews</dt></dl>
<p><small><b>Books</b></small>
</p>
<ul><li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1238218222" /><cite id="CITEREFIqbal2009" class="citation book cs1">Iqbal, Muzaffar (2009). <i>Islam, Science, Muslims, and Technology</i>. Islamabad: Dost. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0-9738744-2-6" title="Special:BookSources/978-0-9738744-2-6"><bdi>978-0-9738744-2-6</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx&#95;ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft&#95;val&#95;fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Islam%2C+Science%2C+Muslims%2C+and+Technology&amp;rft.place=Islamabad&amp;rft.pub=Dost&amp;rft.date=2009&amp;rft.isbn=978-0-9738744-2-6&amp;rft.aulast=Iqbal&amp;rft.aufirst=Muzaffar&amp;rfr&#95;id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ASeyyed+Hossein+Nasr" class="Z3988"></span></li>
